----------------------------------------------------------------
PURPOSE
----------------------------------------------------------------
This repository hosts the official TRIZEL website.

The website functions strictly as an epistemic operational portal:
- a read-only aggregation surface,
- a traceable scientific reference,
- a controlled research gateway.

It does NOT generate knowledge.
It exposes, organizes, and audits validated analytical outputs
produced by TRIZEL research repositories.

----------------------------------------------------------------
CORE PRINCIPLES
----------------------------------------------------------------
• Verification-first, not narrative-driven
• Integrator-first system intelligence
• Full provenance and auditability
• No speculative or decorative content
• No editorial authority over scientific results

----------------------------------------------------------------
MULTILINGUAL REQUIREMENT
----------------------------------------------------------------
Public content is provided with full parity in:
- English (EN)
- French (FR)

Rules:
- Every public page exists in both languages
- Identical structure and semantic content
- No language asymmetry is permitted

Violation of language parity blocks deployment.

----------------------------------------------------------------
PUBLISHING RULES
----------------------------------------------------------------
Allowed:
- Declared outputs only
- Version-locked artifacts
- Audit metadata (repository, commit, timestamp, epistemic status)

Forbidden:
- Placeholder content
- Draft or speculative material
- Undeclared artifacts
- Informal or marketing language

Any violation blocks deployment.

----------------------------------------------------------------
REPOSITORY ROLE
----------------------------------------------------------------
This repository is a VIEWER / AGGREGATOR ONLY.

It must not:
- perform analysis,
- generate results,
- reinterpret data,
- modify scientific outputs.

All intelligence originates upstream from
registered TRIZEL research repositories.

